quran[7]{c,v,t}:
  9,62,"They swear to you by God, to please you; but God and His Messenger -- more right is it they should please Him, if they are believers"
  9,63,"Do they not know that whosoever opposes God and His Messenger -- for him awaits the fire of Gehenna, therein to dwell forever? That is the mighty degradation"
  9,64,"The hypocrites are afraid, lest a sura should be sent down against them, telling thee what is in their hearts. Say: 'Mock on; God will bring forth what you fear"
  9,65,"And if thou questionest them, then assuredly they will say, 'We were only plunging and playing.' Say: 'What, then were you mocking God, and His signs, and His Messenger"
  9,66,"Make no excuses. You have disbelieved after your believing. If We forgive one party of you, We will chastise another party for that they were sinners"
  9,67,"The hypocrites, the men and the women, are as one another; they bid to dishonour, and forbid honour; they keep their hands shut; they have forgotten God, and He has forgotten them. The hypocrites -- they are the ungodly"
  9,68,"God has promised the hypocrites, men and women, and the unbelievers, the fire of Gehenna, therein to dwell foreover. That is enough for them; God has cursed them; and there awaits them Like a lasting chastisement"